94
00:05:03,577 --> 00:05:05,517
and we're off to the races.

95
00:05:05,517 --> 00:05:11,539
Now, we design our games around a paradigm that we call the active cinematic experience.

96
00:05:11,539 --> 00:05:13,720
Active being the key.

97
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,721
We like to keep things on the stick,

98
00:05:15,721 --> 00:05:18,822
because we feel that moments conveyed through gameplay have a bigger impact.

99
00:05:20,052 --> 00:05:23,093
And we aim to sell a single cohesive story,

100
00:05:23,093 --> 00:05:24,454
no branching narratives.

101
00:05:24,454 --> 00:05:26,114
We do allow a lot of player agency

102
00:05:26,114 --> 00:05:28,855
within the confines of a level and the gameplay mechanics,

103
00:05:28,855 --> 00:05:32,357
but we cannot let them affect the outcome of the story.

104
00:05:32,357 --> 00:05:35,918
And we call this the wide linear approach.

105
00:05:35,918 --> 00:05:38,039
But since we know where the character and the player

106
00:05:38,039 --> 00:05:39,139
are going to be at all times,

107
00:05:39,139 --> 00:05:41,160
we can plot the character relationship

108
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:42,420
and write accordingly,

109
00:05:42,420 --> 00:05:43,881
and we can tailor the visuals and narrative

110
00:05:43,881 --> 00:05:45,001
